    <p class="text">
      This project uses an AI image-making model (a latent text-to-image diffusion model) trained on a custom dataset to generate a localized and seasonal camouflage pattern. The dataset is comprised of around 400 of my own photos taken at Davis Memorial Wildlife Refuge in East Greenwich, Rhode Island. 
    </p>
    <p class="text">
      The refuge is 40 acres of forest and wetland with a small trail that brushes up against the Hunt river. It’s the smallest of fourteen wildlife refuges owned by the Audubon Society of Rhode Island, making it the smallest actively conserved piece of nature in the smallest U.S. state.
    </p>
