    <p class="text">
      The dataset was composed of ~400 images taken at Davis Memorial Wildlife Refuge in late November. This was used to train a Stable Diffusion 1.5 model using the LoRA method (Low Rank Adaptation of Large Language Models). From this trained model, many outputs were generated, testing different generation parameters and prompting techniques. Around 50% of the outputs I considered unusable, and another 40% usuable but not functional (i.e. not very effective as camouflage when overlaid on images from the original dataset). From the remaining 10% came a range of styles from abstract to naturalistic that were acceptably functional. The final pattern I chose for its naturalism and also its flexibilty - it worked well overlaid on a large percentage of the original images.
    </p>

